#importing datasets into dataframes and string in dictionary
import os

path = r"/content/drive/MyDrive/Data/Cost_report"
file_names = os.listdir(path)
dicta = {}
for filename in file_names:
    if filename.endswith(".csv"):
        df = filename.split('.csv')[0]
        paths = os.path.join(path, filename)
        dicta[df] = pd.read_csv(paths, encoding='latin-1')

#combining datasets and creating a new column for year
cost_report = ['2015_CostReport', '2016_CostReport', '2017_CostReport', '2018_CostReport' ,'2019_CostReport', '2020_CostReport', '2021_CostReport']

cost = []
for names in cost_report:
    if names in dicta:
        dicta[names]['Year'] = int(names[:4])
        cost.append(dicta[names])

costreport = pd.concat(cost, ignore_index=True)

from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

# Initialize the decision tree model
dt_model = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)
# Fit the decision tree model to the training data
dt_model.fit(X_train_dropna, y_train_dropna)
# Predict on the training and testing sets
dt_train_preds = dt_model.predict(X_train_dropna)
dt_test_preds = dt_model.predict(X_test_dropna)
# Calculate accuracy for decision tree
dt_train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_dropna, dt_train_preds)
dt_test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test.loc[X_test_dropna.index], dt_test_preds)

# Initialize the random forest model
rf_model = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42)
# Fit the random forest model to the training data
rf_model.fit(X_train_dropna, y_train_dropna)
# Predict on the training and testing sets
rf_train_preds = rf_model.predict(X_train_dropna)
rf_test_preds = rf_model.predict(X_test_dropna)
# Calculate accuracy for random forest
rf_train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_dropna, rf_train_preds)
rf_test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test.loc[X_test_dropna.index], rf_test_preds)

# Predict on the training set for logistic regression to compare training performance
logreg_train_preds = logreg.predict(X_train_dropna)

# Prepare data for plotting
model_names = ['Decision Tree', 'Random Forest', 'Logistic Regression']
train_accuracies = [dt_train_accuracy, rf_train_accuracy, accuracy_score(y_train_dropna, logreg_train_preds)]
test_accuracies = [dt_test_accuracy, rf_test_accuracy, accuracy]

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.barh(model_names, train_accuracies, label='Train Accuracy')
plt.barh(model_names, test_accuracies, label='Test Accuracy')
plt.xlabel('Accuracy')
plt.title('Model Comparison: Train and Test Accuracy')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
